{{Short description|Maldivian politician}}
'''Dr. Mohamed Shafeeq''' is a [[Maldivians|Maldivian]] politician. He is the incumbent Finance Minister of the Maldives.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nov 17 |first=0 |last2=2023 19:31 |title=Dr. Muizzu’s promising cabinet |url=https://en.sun.mv/85974 |access-date=2023-11-18 |website=SunOnline International |language=en}}</ref> He was the Chief Financial Officer of Housing Development Finance Corporation (HDFC). He joined the corporation in 2009, and was appointed to the post of CFO in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Reehaan |first=Mohamed |date=2023-11-18 |title=President Muizzu appoints Saeed as Economic Minister, Shafeeq as Finance Minister |url=https://mbt.mv/president-muizzu-appoints-saeed-as-economic-minister-shafeeq-as-finance-minister/ |access-date=2023-11-18 |website=Maldives Business Times |language=en-US}}</ref>

He completed his PhD in Business Administration from the [[IIC University of Technology]], [[Cambodia]], via the European Institute of Professional Education in Sri Lanka.<ref>{{Cite web |last=frontpage.mv |title=President Dr. Muizzu Has Appointed the New Cabinet |url=https://www.frontpage.mv/news/detail/787 |access-date=2023-11-18 |website=frontpage.mv |language=en}}</ref>
